cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.CR 

This paper deals with wireless powered sensor networks and communication techniques to resolve collisions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory and signal processing, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second likely category. The use of analytical expressions and mathematical models indicates cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as a possible category. The paper also deals with interference cancellation, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of backscatter communications, which suggests cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as a possible category.
